FBIS4-39956 "drsov113_b_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Moscow Poll: Yeltsin Still Most Popular Politician Moscow Poll: Yeltsin Still Most Popular Politician LD1106205494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 11 Jun 94 LD1106205494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Boris Yeltsin is still the most popular Russian politician, according to a public opinion poll carried out in Moscow in the run-up to independence day, by the Institute of Sociology and Parliamentarism. At the same time, the number of people in the capital who agree with, or express some positive interest in, the president's policies is down from 55 percent in May 1991 to 28 percent in May this year. The number of Muscovites who do not agree with the president's policies has increased from 13 to 23 percent over this period.
